transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Thanks for calling Viagra, this is Charles.

Speaker 2: Hi there, how are we doing today?

Speaker 1: I'm good, how about yourself?

Speaker 2: Doing okay. I need to cancel my subscription.

Speaker 1: Okay, I got Ken Greek in Troutville, Virginia.

Speaker 2: Yeah, I've just gotten a notice that there's a shipment that is on its way,

Speaker 1: and because of the weather it was delayed.

Speaker 2: It reminded me that I need to cancel that.

Speaker 1: Yeah, it looks like you're a VIP member here, Ken.

Speaker 2: Last time you called in was in July,

Speaker 1: and I'm not sure if you remember the conversation or not,

Speaker 2: but the notes that I see with the gentleman you were speaking with,

Speaker 1: it says that to keep the VIP membership,

Speaker 2: we send everything once or twice a year now,

Speaker 1: and you're able to order them as needed.

Speaker 2: So you're not getting them every single month?

Speaker 1: This is only refill from now until July.

Speaker 2: It's only every six months.

Speaker 1: Are you just not using them?

Speaker 2: Well, it's medically not safe for me to use.

Speaker 1: I get you.

Speaker 2: I had a heart attack.

Speaker 1: Okay, understood.

Speaker 2: I asked him about it, and he said no under no circumstances.

Speaker 1: Understood.

Speaker 2: Okay, so I'll cancel everything going forward.

Speaker 1: The ones that are on their way,

Speaker 2: I'm not sure when they're going to arrive because of all the snow that's happening,

Speaker 1: but when it does, don't rip it up.

Speaker 2: Don't tear it up.

Speaker 1: Don't do anything.

Speaker 2: Just shake it and confirm that there's pills in there,

Speaker 1: and then with a marker or pen, just write return to sender on it,

Speaker 2: put it back in the mailbox.

Speaker 1: Mailman will come by next day, take it, send it back to us.

Speaker 2: He'll get the money back, okay?

Speaker 1: Sounds like a plan.

Speaker 2: Thank you very much.

Speaker 1: Absolutely.

Speaker 2: All right, Ken.

Speaker 1: Good luck in the future, brother.

Speaker 2: Okay, you too.

Speaker 1: Bye.

Speaker 2: All right.

Speaker 1: Thank you.

Speaker 2: Bye-bye.
